question: Which on of the following is the correct sequence in the descending order of precedence in the warrant of precedence?
option1: Attorney General of India-Judges of the supreme Court - Members of Parliament-Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha
option2: Judges of the Supreme Court-Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha-Attorney General of India-Members of Parliament
option3: Attorney General of India-Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha-Judges of the Supreme Court-Members of Parliament
option4: Judges of the Supreme Court-Attorney General of India-Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha- Members of Parliament
answer: Judges of the Supreme Court-Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha-Attorney General of India-Members of Parliament
explanation: Judges of the Supreme Court - Deputy Chairman of Rajya Sabha - Attorney General of India - Members of Parliament.
